## Key Insights

- Popular tracks tend to cluster within certain artists, indicating repeat success
- High-energy songs often appear frequently among more popular tracks
- Danceability varies across artists but remains a key characteristic of popular music
- The longest tracks are not necessarily the most popular
- Aggregated metrics help reveal overall trends in music production and listener preferences

